me.Abhigya.core.util.math

Class Vector3D

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.Abhigya.core.util.math.Vector3D
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vector, org.bukkit.configuration.serialization.ConfigurationSerializable

    public class Vector3D
extends java.lang.Object
implements Vector
    Encapsulates an immutable cached Vector of three dimensions ( x, y and z ).

    The values of length(), lengthSquared(), normalize() and hashCode() are cached for a better performance.

      • length

        public float length()
        Description copied from interface: Vector
        Gets the magnitude of the Vector, defined as sqrt ( x^2 + y^2 + z^2 ). The value of this method is cached, so repeatedly calling this method to get the vector's magnitude will not re-calculate it. NaN will be returned if the inner result of the sqrt() function overflows, which will be caused if the length is too long.

        This is the equivalent of using: 

        Math.sqrt ( Vector.lengthSquared() )

        Specified by:
        length in interface Vector
        Returns:
        Magnitude

      • toVector2D

        public Vector2D toVector2D(int x,
                           int y)
        Creates and returns a new Vector2D by specifying the components to provide, following the rules explain below: 
        -1 represents the value of getX() in this
 vector.
        0 represents the value of getY() in this
 vector.
        1 represents the value of getZ() in this
 vector.

        Parameters:
        x - Providing -1, will construct the Vector2D with its x component having the same value as the x component of this vector. Providing 0, will construct the Vector2D with its x component having the same value as the y component of this vector. Providing 1, will construct the Vector2D with its x component having the same value as the z component of this vector.
        y - Providing -1, will construct the Vector2D with its y component having the same value as the x component of this vector. Providing 0, will construct the Vector2D with its y component having the same value as the y component of this vector. Providing 1, will construct the Vector2D with its y component having the same value as the z component of this vector.
        Returns:
        2D version
